Tweet text: Another take on #CitizenScience from Michael Poulsen of https://t.co/U4qJxXZHdy: #CruiseShips! "Tourists find it meaningful to contribute to science" while they're on their holiday. Highlighting #data collected and submitted to @happyhumpback. #AOS2020 https://t.co/htFQ5TbkI3

Ann Garland of https://t.co/lnetu0egqL showcasing the #CommunityMonitoring powers of #CitizenScience to collect #data related to #Arctic #CoastalErosion - "the wave of the future" to keep the community involved with their own needs. 
@arcticchange1 #AOS2020 https://t.co/CTyfPqLIVU

@Gruene_Partei with a fascinating talk on #interdisciplinarity in the #Arctic: #ComputerScience, #NaturalScience, and #SocialScience can use the strength of EACH discipline to address complex problems like monitoring #ClimateChange. #AOS2020 @arcticchange1 #SynthesisScience
Participating now in #workinggroup 2 - learning about how the data collected by https://t.co/vdvS7bX9LJ sites informs #SearchandRescue operations in the #Arctic! #AOS2020 @arcticchange1
@metaarctic: "We need a structured, collaborative interface to link societal needs with observing and data system requirements." #AOS2020 @arcticchange1 #VirtualMeeting https://t.co/Lybbsx7Jct

Now we're hearing from @metaarctic about the ROADS initiative - focused on promoting free and ethically #OpenAccess to all #Arctic #data. Exciting project to work on through participation in #AOS2020! @arcticchange1

Our own @metamattj on #federatedsearch and science on https://t.co/H3y1ZpEVEw: "Whenever you try to build a federated catalog, you find out how many different ways people can interpret the same fields." #AOS2020 #interoperability

Next up, a talk from Henrik Steen Anderson about Copernicus, an in-situ service from the #EU that transforms information from multiple sources, including satellites, into operational services for #EarthObservation and specifically #ArcticObservation. @arcticchange1 #AOS2020

Attending the #workinggroup4 on #federateddata and #interoperability and learning about the many other organizations including @CAFFSecretariat collecting and archiving data like the @arcticdatactr- almost 350k occurrence records in their system! #AOS2020 @arcticchange1

Up very early - 1 am Pacific time! - for the first #workinggroup session of #AOS2020! I'll be tweeting in real time from #ASSW2020 all week. #VirtualConference #Arctic #ArcticObservingSummit @arcticchange1
Several of our @arcticdatactr team members will be there - looking forward to a great #AOS2020 online! https://t.co/YwjwUOqohi

For this #SharingSciFri, we'd like to highlight a new paper on how #beaver dams in the #Arctic control surface water and thermokarst dynamics - and you can check out the data from @TundraTime & team on https://t.co/1er02fWPFB.  https://t.co/Pp5znoZ4Pl https://t.co/ep3KCzWpHY
Over here we're rooting for the #Arctic! #teamArctic #GlacierGladness #Alaska https://t.co/ocr3V9XfWS

With many #fieldwork trips being cancelled or postponed, we're seeing lots of datasets being submitted to the #Arctic Data Center! Keep 'em coming and we'll have a round up every Friday of #newdata to explore. #datascience #openscience
We'll be there! Thanks for all the hard work you all did to put these meeting online. https://t.co/i6wSgZaoK1
Now that's some #distancing! Beautiful view, thanks for sharing. #arctic #science https://t.co/QxmR22rJRq

Explore the Arctic from the comfort of your couch! The @MOSAiCArctic has launched a new online open course, Frozen in the Ice: Exploring the Arctic, featuring 50 videos from MOSAiC #scientists and #Arctic experts - check it out here. https://t.co/VrVs7jfsIy

Working from home? Want to escape (temporarily)? Listen to the sounds of Arctic #marinemammals and a deeper discussion of using #bioacoustics to better understand how ship sounds can affect #Arctic wildlife. @mongabay  https://t.co/ORXkxJE388

Check out this great paper that just came out from some of our close colleagues at @ESIPfed - this #data #riskassessment framework is important for #datapreservation and #datastewardship. #datalibs #newpaper https://t.co/2JoEsoFTJc

Calling #Arctic researchers - Do you want to tackle your research data management skills? Work in a more open, efficient and reproducible way? Apply by April 24th to join our funded Data Science Training workshop in October. Details at: https://t.co/E1Hcne0FIS https://t.co/oNqUL372nC
